The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Court video 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Court video 
                            
	New Delhi, April 25: The Supreme Court has agreed to examine a plea to videotape court proceedings.         
	Raise this plea in the case (on judicial reforms) pending before the court. We will hear it, a two-judge bench headed by Chief Justice K.G. Balakrishnan said on Monday.         
	A Chandigarh advocate, R.T.P.S. Tulsi, had asked for the proceedings of Punjab and Haryana High Court to be videographed for record and transparency.                                                                                                                                                                          
